textAnnotations.description:
He had almost entirely settled book into his old
ways, even to reading the about two hours each
day. Though be did not refuse wine, which the
judge aboys hand on the table at dinner, he
did not act as though he found it recessary
except in moderate compliance with his father's
habit.
